value.value: A very rare morphologic variant of glomus tumor with a size greater than 2 cm.  The tumor arises in subfascial or visceral tissues. It is characterized by the presence of atypical mitotic figures, or marked nuclear atypia, or the combination of both.  It has an aggressive clinical course.

A morphologic variant of the glomus tumor characterized by the presence of dilated veins, surrounded by small clusters of glomus cells. Glomangiomas are most often present in patients with multiple lesions.

A morphologic variant of the glomus tumor with architectural features similar to solid glomus tumor.  It is characterized by the presence of elongated glomus cells which resemble mature smooth muscle.
